{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17587168","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17587168"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15122"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588278","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588278"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:05:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:05:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15122"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15122","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15122"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.33,0,0,0.14,0.52]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7810"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64902"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7810","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7810"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15122"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50336"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"10001"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19043"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19047"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21544"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64902","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64902"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EOdynophagia is a common presenting symptom in gastrointestinal medicine.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes odynophagia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Difficulty initiating a swallow","Pain occurring between meals","Regurgitation of undigested food","Sensation of food sticking in the chest","Sharp pain occurring during swallowing"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EOdynophagia refers to \u003Cstrong\u003Esharp pain occurring during swallowing\u003C/strong\u003E. It is distinct from \u003Cstrong\u003Edifficulty initiating a swallow\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Esensation of food sticking in the chest\u003C/strong\u003E, which are symptoms of dysphagia. \u003Cstrong\u003EPain occurring between meals\u003C/strong\u003E may suggest other conditions like gastro-oesophageal reflux disease. \u003Cstrong\u003ERegurgitation of undigested food\u003C/strong\u003E is a separate symptom that may occur with conditions like achalasia.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EOdynophagia typically indicates an inflammatory or ulcerative process in the oesophagus, such as oesophagitis, ulceration, or infection. Common causes include viral or fungal infections (especially in immunocompromised patients), caustic ingestion, or severe reflux disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Odynophagia is pain during swallowing and indicates inflammation or ulceration in the oesophagus","Odynophagia differs from dysphagia which is difficulty swallowing"],"references":["Patel H, Nguyen SMT, Haque A, Krishnaswamy G. Odynophagia in a young adult: revisiting herpetic esophagitis and eosinophilic esophagitis. BMJ Case Rep. 2022 Nov 11;15(11):e251238. doi: 10.1136/bcr-2022-251238. PMID: 36368731; PMCID: PMC9660505.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Panebianco M, Marchese-Ragona R, Masiero S, Restivo DA. Dysphagia in neurological diseases: a literature review. Neurol Sci. 2020 Nov;41(11):3067-3073. doi: 10.1007/s10072-020-04495-2. Epub 2020 Jun 7. PMID: 32506360; PMCID: PMC7567719","Wilkinson JM, Codipilly DC, Wilfahrt RP. Dysphagia: Evaluation and Collaborative Management. Am Fam Physician. 2021 Jan 15;103(2):97-106. PMID: 33448766"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50336"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15122"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50336","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50336"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-24T21:28:19+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-24T21:28:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7810"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64902"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving info